          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and recitation and is a late Vedic work, a philosophical treatise that reinterprets the symbolic value of Hindu rites and rituals, but points especially to the centrality of the Vedic god Rudra, an early form of the Hindu deity Śiva, within the constructed universe.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Atharvaśiropaniṣad</title>
              <title type="vernacular">अथर्वशिरोपनिषद्</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: ity atharvaśiropaniṣat // oṃ bhadraṃkarṇebhiḥ // svastinaṃ // (f. 5v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
